            "category": "Information Disclosure",
            "title": "Unvalidated Input to Lambda Function",
            "description": "HTTP API routes requests to Lambda without input validation or sanitization at the API Gateway layer. The Lambda receives raw query parameters from route_key=GET /users; an attacker can inject malicious input (SQL injection, path traversal) that the Lambda handler may not validate, exposing user data or enabling further attacks.",
            "severity": "High"
          },
          {
            "category": "Tampering",
            "title": "Lambda Payload Format Version 2.0 Allows Unvalidated Headers",
            "description": "Integration uses payload_format_version=2.0, which passes raw HTTP headers and request context to Lambda. Attacker can craft malicious HTTP headers (Host, User-Agent, X-Forwarded-For) to manipulate Lambda logic if handler does not validate headers, leading to request forgery or cache poisoning.",
            "severity": "Medium"
          }
        ]
      }
